Program: Outlook
Title: Healing Hate in Bosnia
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02b23k8
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 13 Nov 2014
Vahidin Omanovic is a Bosnian imam who has been trying to breach religious and ethnic divides in his home town. Nimesh Patel is a successful rap artist who has turned his back on the trappings of Western status, and is working with slum children in India. Plus, survivors of tiger attacks in the Sundarbans region of Bangladesh tell their stories to the BBC's Candida Beveridge. Show less